				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So wait, it can actually access the full spectrum of 15-bit color?  And eight palettes for sprites and BG each? Holy crap!<br />I suppose I shouldn't be too surprised, since the GBC came out in the era of the Nintendo 64, and it wouldn't exactly be hard to up the stats at least just a little, but still, I've long been under the assumption that the Game Boy was roughly the same as the NES, minus color, and the Game Boy Color was basically the same hardware but with color added.<br /><br />...How do these stats compare to the original Game Boy?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
